  abstract = {In this paper we are interested in the long time behaviour of the positive solutions of the mutation selection model with Neumann Boundary condition: \$\$ {\textbackslash}frac\{{\textbackslash}partial u(x,t)\}\{dt\}=u{\textbackslash}left[r(x)-{\textbackslash}int\_\{{\textbackslash}O\}K(x,y){\textbar}u{\textbar}{\textasciicircum}\{p\}(y){\textbackslash},dy{\textbackslash}right]+{\textbackslash}nabla{\textbackslash}cdot{\textbackslash}left(A(x){\textbackslash}nabla u(x){\textbackslash}right),{\textbackslash}qquad {\textbackslash}text\{in\}{\textbackslash}quad {\textbackslash}R{\textasciicircum}+{\textbackslash}times{\textbackslash}O\$\$ where \${\textbackslash}O{\textbackslash}subset {\textbackslash}R{\textasciicircum}N\$ is a bounded smooth domain, \$k(.,.) {\textbackslash}in C({\textbackslash}bar {\textbackslash}O {\textbackslash}times C({\textbackslash}bar{\textbackslash}O), {\textbackslash}R), p{\textbackslash}ge 1\$ and \$A(x)\$ is a smooth elliptic matrix. In a blind competition situation, i.e \$K(x,y)=k(y)\$, we show the existence of a unique positive steady state which is positively globally stable. That is, the positive steady state attracts all the possible trajectories initiated from any non negative initial datum. When \$K\$ is a general positive kernel, we also present a necessary and sufficient condition for the existence of a positive steady states. We prove also some stability result on the dynamic of the equation when the competition kernel \$K\$ is of the form \$K(x,y)=k\_0(y)+{\textbackslash}eps k\_1(x,y)\$. That is, we prove that for sufficiently small \${\textbackslash}eps\$ there exists a unique steady state, which in addition is positively asymptotically stable. The proofs of the global stability of the steady state essentially rely on non-linear relative entropy identities and an orthogonal decomposition. These identities combined with the decomposition provide us some a priori estimates and differential inequalities essential to characterise the asymptotic behaviour of the solutions.},
